1. => What is the difference between Properties And Attributes in Javascript.
Answer => Attributes => HTML attributes are used to provide additional information about an HTML element. 
                        They are specified in the opening tag of the element and are always strings.
                        (===> It is read only properties.)


Properties => DOM properties are the values that can be accessed and modified through the DOM with JavaScript. 
              They can be of any type, including strings, numbers, objects, and functions.

